        legend.position = "right")
```

**Key insight:** The continental U.S. is overwhelmingly pale yellow, confirming near-universal access in most counties. The Alaska inset and the Southwest cluster stand out as the two structural outliers — the most affected communities are small in population, which is why the national aggregate rate remains low despite the severity of local conditions.

