**Key insight:** `r sum(water_change$direction == "Improved")` counties improved and `r sum(water_change$direction == "Worsened")` worsened between 2022 and 2023. The split is nearly balanced, indicating aggregate stability. Extreme changes (> 5 pp) are more plausibly driven by ACS sampling variance in small counties than by genuine infrastructure shifts — underscoring the fragility of progress without sustained investment.

